@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxDialog))]

<ApiDoc Type="typeof(HxDialog)">

	<DocAlert Type="DocAlertType.Warning">
		Bootstrap only supports one dialog window at a time. Nested dialogs aren't supported as they are believed to provide a poor user experience.
	</DocAlert>

    <DocHeading Title="Basic usage" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxDialog_Demo)" Tabs="false" />

    <DocHeading Title="Static backdrop" />
	<p>When the backdrop is set to <code>DialogBackdrop.Static</code>, the dialog will not close when clicking outside of it.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxDialog_Demo_Backdrop)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Scrolling long content" />
	<p>When dialogs become too long for the user's viewport or device, they scroll independently of the page itself. Try the demo below to see what we mean.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxDialog_Demo_Scrolling)" />

	<p>You can also create a scrollable dialog that allows scrolling the dialog body by setting the <code>Scrollable</code> parameter.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxDialog_Demo_Scrollable)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Vertical centering" />
	<p>Dialogs are vertically centered natively, there is no parameter to set. The dialog is built on the native <code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code> element, which the browser centers in the viewport by default.</p>

    <DocHeading Title="Animation" />
	<p>Use the <code>Animation</code> parameter to choose the open/close animation of the dialog. The default is <code>DialogAnimation.Fade</code>, use <code>DialogAnimation.None</code> to disable the animation.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxDialog_Demo_Animation)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Swapping dialogs" />
	<p>When a button inside an open dialog opens another dialog, the dialogs <strong>swap</strong> &ndash; the first one closes as the second one opens, and the backdrop stays visible the whole time without flickering. Just call <code>ShowAsync()</code> on the other dialog; you don't need to close the current one first.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxDialog_Demo_Swapping)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Non-modal dialogs" />
	<p>Set <code>NonModal="true"</code> to open the dialog with the browser-native <code>show()</code> instead of <code>showModal()</code>. A non-modal dialog has no backdrop, no focus trap, and does not block the rest of the page.</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxDialog_Demo_NonModal)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Optional sizes" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxDialog_Demo_Size)" />

    <DocHeading Title="Fullscreen dialog" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxDialog_Demo_Fullscreen)" />
</ApiDoc>